{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}} {{Infobox university | name = Aarhus School of Architecture | native_name = Arkitektskolen Aarhus | latin_name = | image_name = Raaes House Aarhus A.jpeg | image_size = 250px | motto = | mottoeng = | established = 1965 | type = Public university | staff = | faculty = | rector = Torben Nielsen | students = 750 | city = [[Aarhus]] | state = | country = Denmark {{flagicon|Denmark}} | campus = Aarhus | affiliations = | logo = | website = [http://aarch.dk/ Aarhus School of Architecture] }}
The '''Aarhus School of Architecture''' (Arkitektskolen Aarhus) was founded in 1965 in [[Aarhus]], Denmark. Along with the [[Royal Danish Academy of Fine Arts]], School of Architecture in [[Copenhagen]], it is responsible for the education of [[architect]]s in Denmark. The school has approximately 750 students.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.denstoredanske.dk/Kunst_og_kultur/Arkitektur/Arkitekturinstitutioner/Arkitektskolen_Aarhus |title=Arkitektskolen Aarhus |publisher=Gyldendal |accessdate=7 February 2010 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090907084959/http://www.denstoredanske.dk/Kunst_og_kultur/Arkitektur/Arkitekturinstitutioner/Arkitektskolen_Aarhus |archivedate=7 September 2009 |df=}}</ref>
== Educational structure and content == Teaching at the Aarhus School of Architecture is studio-based, emphasising group work and project work. The school places an emphasis on practice-based teaching, while maintaining an artistic approach to architecture. Teaching is organised around a number of research labs, based on on-going and close dialogue with teachers.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://aarch.dk/info/organisation/staff-2/platforms/ |title=Discipline-specific platforms |publisher=Aarhus School of Architecture |accessdate=5 November 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304095455/http://aarch.dk/info/organisation/staff-2/platforms/ |archivedate=4 March 2016 |df= }}</ref> Workshop facilities allow students to explore their ideas in 3D and in 1:1. Other resources include a specialised library, a materials shop and a [http://aarch.dk/info/school-web/fabrication-labs/robot-lab/ robot lab].
In 2016 the school's research was restructured as three [http://aarch.dk/info/research/about-research/research-labs/ research labs]:
Research Lab 1: Territories, Architecture, and Transformation
Research Lab 2: Technology and Building Cultures
Research Lab 3: Emerging Architecture
Research is carried out within the school’s three focus areas: habitation, transformation, and sustainability – as well as in the field of research by design.
Besides Bachelor’s, Master’s and PhD programmes the school offers supplementary education for architects and similar professional groups at various levels. Research at the school is also to a high degree practice-based, i.e. based on cooperation with architectural practices located internationally and locally. The high concentration of architectural practices in Aarhus provides a sound basis for this cooperation.<ref>Arkitekturklyngen i Århus, p. 14</ref>
The Aarhus School of Architecture is an educational institution under the [http://en.fivu.dk/ Danish Ministry for Science, Innovation and Higher Education].
== School buildings == The school is situated in the [[Nørre Stenbro]] neighborhood on ''Nørreport''. The campus comprises the [[Listed buildings in Aarhus Municipality|listed building]] known as Raae's House ({{lang-da|Raaes Gård}}) from 1798 and a newer building from 1997 with [[auditorium]] and an exhibition hall.<ref name="Ark" />
Raae's House is a brick building in [[Neoclassical architecture|Neoclassical style]] built by Hans Fridrich Raae, one of the foremost merchants in the city during the 18th century.<ref name="StatArk">{{cite web |url=http://aarhuswiki.dk/wiki/N%C3%B8rreport_20 |title=Nørreport 20 |publisher=Aarhus State Archives |language=Danish |accessdate=6 February 2016 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6f6rxg9Q1?url=http://aarhuswiki.dk/wiki/N%C3%B8rreport_20 |archive-date=7 February 2016 |dead-url=no |df=}}</ref> It was originally built on the northern edge of the city by the city walls on what was at the time [[Studsgade]]. It is one of the best examples of Neoclassical architecture in Aarhus and one of the last remaining brick built merchant's houses of that time. The building is in 4 wings with a [[courtyard]] in the middle but only the house facing the street is constructed in brick with the remaining being [[half-timbered]] structures with [[Baroque architecture|Baroque]] elements. The building was listed in 1919.<ref name="Kult">{{cite web |url=https://www.kulturarv.dk/fbb/sagvis.pub?sag=1097021 |title=Raaes Gård |publisher=[[Danish Heritage Agency]] |language=Danish |accessdate=6 February 2016 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6f6rqcNwy?url=https://www.kulturarv.dk/fbb/sagvis.pub?sag=1097021 |archive-date=7 February 2016 |dead-url=no |df=}}</ref><ref name="Ark">{{cite web |url=http://www.arkark.dk/building.aspx?buildingid=3627 |title=Arkitektskolen (Raaes Gård), Aarhus |publisher=ArkArk |language=Danish |accessdate=6 February 2016 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6f6s6fnA4?url=http://www.arkark.dk/building.aspx?buildingid=3627 |archive-date=7 February 2016 |dead-url=yes |df=}}</ref><ref name="GIS">{{cite web |url=http://gis.aarhus.dk/kommuneatlas/registranter/stenbro/side9.htm |title=REGISTRANT – Registrantområder – Nørre Stenbro og Skovvejskvarteret |publisher=[[Aarhus Municipality]] |language=Danish |accessdate=6 February 2016 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6f6s8jBq7?url=http://gis.aarhus.dk/kommuneatlas/registranter/stenbro/side9.htm |archive-date=7 February 2016 |dead-url=yes |df=}}</ref>
In 1997 the architects firm [[Kjaer & Richter]] built an addition on an adjacent plot of land. It was designed in a modernistic style of concrete with glass facade. It is structured as a rectangular, black box with a dominating glass facade facing the street, intentionally contrasting the old building next to it. The design is modelled as a house-in-house with the auditorium appearing like an interior island that divides the building in an exhibition hall and [[foyer]].<ref name="Ark" />
