'''''The World of Robert Burns''''' is [[educational software]] which teaches about the life and times of [[Robert Burns]]. It was launched to coincide with the 200th anniversary of Burns's death. The software was awarded ''Gold'' by ''[[Acorn User]]'' magazine.<ref name="tes chapter verse">{{cite news | url=http://www.tes.co.uk/article.aspx?storycode=15328 | title=History in chapter and verse | work=[[Times Educational Supplement]] | date=October 20, 1995 | accessdate=December 30, 2011 | author=Lamond, Catherine | quote=The launch of The World of Robert Burns CD-Rom in 1996 marks the 200th anniversary of the death of Scotland's national bard. [...] The disc has already won a gold award from Acorn User magazine.}}</ref>

It was developed by Cambridge Software House in associate with [[Galloway Education Authority]], and featured poems, letters, music, photographs and videos.<ref>{{cite web|title=History in chapterand verse|url=http://www.tes.co.uk/article.aspx?storycode=15328|publisher=Times Education Supplement|accessdate=20 February 2014}}</ref>

